              		<p><a href="../parents.htm">Parents of Penguins</a> &gt; Privacy Protection</p>
              		<p class="lg_title"><img src="images/privacy.gif" align="right" />Privacy Protection</p>
              		<ul>
                        <li><a href="#info-we-collect" >The  Information We Collect</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#use-info" >How We  Use the Information</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#collect-third-party" >Collection of Information for Third-Party Sites and Sponsors</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#cookies" >Cookies</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#security" >Security</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#financial-info" >Financial  Information</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#parental-review" >Parental  Review of Information</strong></a></li>
                        <li><a href="#contact-us" >Contact  Us</strong></a></li>
              		</ul>
                  	<p>Club Penguin is committed to providing a fun, entertaining, and safe  website for people of all ages. </p>
                  	<p>We are dedicated to safeguarding any personal information collected online  and we ensure that our privacy policy and our information practices adhere to  the U.S. Department of Commerce's Safe Harbor Principles and the Canadian Code  of Practice. </p>
                  	<p>We take special measures to help children protect their privacy while  online. For example, we do not ask children to disclose more personal  information than is necessary for them to participate in a particular activity,  and we take efforts to prevent children from posting contact information.</p>
                  	<p>&nbsp;</p>
                  	<p>&nbsp;</p>
                  	<h2><strong><a name="info-we-collect" id="info-we-collect"></a>1. The  Information We Collect</strong></h2>
					<blockquote>
                		<p>The only personally identifiable information we  collect from users 12 years old and younger is a parent's valid email address,  which is used to send a single message for Club Penguin account activation                <a href="../privacy.htm#info_we_collect" >  Read More</a>.</p>
			  		</blockquote>
              		<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
              
              		<h2><strong><a name="use-info" id="use-info"></a>2. How We  Use the Information</strong></h2>
              		<blockquote>
                		<p>The information we collect will only be used to  improve the design and content of our site, and to occasionally offer relevant  products, programs, and services.</p>
                		<p>We will never disclose the information we collect,  except when required to do so by law, for example, in response to a court order  or a subpoena.  <a href="../privacy.htm#use_info" >Read More</a>. </p>
              		</blockquote>
              		<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
                    
                  	<h2><strong><a name="collect-third-party" id="collect-third-party"></a>3.  Collection of Information for Third-Party Sites and Sponsors</strong></h2>
                  	<blockquote>
                    	<p>We do not allow third-party companies to solicit or  advertise to our users. </p>
                  	</blockquote>
                  	<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
                  
                  	<h2><strong><a name="cookies" id="cookies"></a>4. Cookies</strong></h2>
                  	<blockquote>
                    	<p>Club Penguin uses &quot;cookies&quot; only to aid in  improving web site design and content. <a href="../privacy.htm#cookies" >Read More</a>. </p>
                  	</blockquote>
                  	<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
                  
                  	<h2><strong><a name="security" id="security"></a>5. Security</strong></h2>
                  	<blockquote>
                    	<p>We have put in place appropriate physical, electronic,  and managerial procedures to safeguard and help prevent unauthorized access,  maintain data security, and correctly use the information we collect online.</p>
                  	</blockquote>
                  	<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
              
              		<h2><strong><a name="financial-info" id="financial-info"></a>6. Financial  Information</strong></h2>
              		<blockquote>
                		<p>The purchase of memberships requires additional  information. That information is stored only by our financial institution and  never used for any other purpose <a href="../privacy.htm#financial_info" >Read More</a>. </p>
              		</blockquote>
              		<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
              
              		<h2><strong><a name="parental-review" id="parental-review"></a>7. Parental  Review of Information</strong></h2>
              		<blockquote>
                		<p>To protect your child's privacy and security, we will  take reasonable steps to help verify your identity before granting you access  to the personal information that we collect and maintain about your child   <a href="../privacy.htm#parental_review" >Read More</a>. </p>
              		</blockquote>
              		<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
              
              		<h2><strong><a name="contact-us" id="contact-us"></a>8. Contact  Us</strong></h2>
                    <blockquote>
                    	<p>Contact the <a href="http://www.clubpenguin.com/contact/privacy_department.htm" ><strong>Privacy Department</strong></a> should you have  any inquiries regarding the privacy policy and/or practices.                                </p>
              		</blockquote>
              		<p align="center"><br />
              			You can read our <a href="../privacy.htm" >full privacy policy here</a>.
                    </p>
